THE IMPRENTA* PROJECT

*(in Spanish/Tagalog: "printing")

created by David Adlao

With over 100+ designs distributed out to various organizations and individuals, we have gained a reputation that screams "quality, creativity, and personality!"

hi!

My name is David Adlao, and as a connoisseur of digital design, I took it to heart when I figured out I could use my skills to help out others looking for a way to express themselves.


It first started out with family, like my cousins, titas (aunts) and titos (uncles), but then I got to making designs for my friends, especially on their birthdays.


But this project doesn't just stop there, no no! I've gathered a team to mass produce designs (and a LOT of T-shirts) for various organizations. Our most recent one was promoting a fundraiser for cancer research.


I have gained a lot of skills throughout this journey of creating and giving, and I hope you enjoy browsing through our collections so you can get a taste of what you're missing out (if you haven't considered us yet)!
